title.narrative: SOCIAL PROTECTION

description.narrative: By 2022, public policies, social protection programmes, and the extreme poverty reduction strategy will have the capacity to monitor investment in children, and respond adequately to the needs of the most vulnerable children, especially adolescent girls., which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Prevention Of Harmful Practice, Reducing Child Poverty, Social Protection. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022 the most vulnerable children and adolescents, and especially girls, will have access to public policies and programmes that promote social inclusion and are supported by Dominican society

description.narrative: After four years of UNICEF’s public advocacy, in January 2021 the President enacted Law 1-21, which prohibits, without exception, legal marriage under the age of 18.; In December,;he launched the;National;Policy for the prevention of,;and attention;and response to, EUs and Adolescent Pregnancy ; to;eradicate;this harmful practice.;Thanks to UNICEF’s support 117,000 high school students had sessions to raise awareness;regarding the prevention of EUs.;UNICEF is supporting shock-responsive social protection services, which influenced the new social protection programme, SUPERATE, to include emergencies as part of its programmatic offer, thus guaranteeing its institutionalization and long-term sustainability.;; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:13/01/2022
